first cycle of </div><div class="t m361 x92 h1e y359 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the dialogue between Job and his friends, Eliphaz was the first </div><div class="t m362 x92 h1e y383 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to answer Job. His answer was followed by Job&apos;s second speech. </div><div class="t m52 x92 h1e y384 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Then another friend, Bildad, jumped into the discussion. Who </div><div class="t m363 xa h1e y385 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was Bildad? &quot;Abraham took a wife, and her name was </div><div class="t m364 xa h1e ya8 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Keturah&quot; (Gen. 25:1). She bore him six children including </div><div class="t m365 x92 h1e y386 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Shuah from whom came the Shuhites. Bildad was a Shuhite. </div><div class="t m154 xa h1e y387 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Abraham sent Keturah&apos;s sons &quot;eastward, unto the east country&quot; </div><div class="t m366 xa h1e y35f ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Gen. 25:6). The Shuhites lived &quot;toward the Euphrates&quot; (Merrill </div><div class="t m367 xa h1e y360 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">F. Unger, </div><div class="t m368 x97 h16 y360 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LInger&apos;s Bible Dictionary </div><div class="t mbd x98 h1e y388 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[Chicago: Moody Press, 1983], </div><div class="t m32e xa h1e y389 ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 1022). Because Bildad shared the misconceptions of his com-</div><div class="t m369 xa h1e y38a ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">panions, it was difficult for him to sympathize with Job. </div><div class="t m368 x6b h1e y38b ff4 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
